# Security Rules

## Never

- Commit secrets, API keys, or `.env` files
- Remove auth middleware from mutating routes
- Trust client-side authorization checks
- Log passwords, session tokens, or API secrets
- Run seed scripts against production databases

## Always

- Validate input with Joi (`schemas.js`) server-side
- Use ownership middleware for edit/delete operations
- Escape user content before embedding in HTML (especially map popups)
- Run `npm audit` when adding dependencies

## Known Critical Issue

`cloudinary-onboarding.js` has hardcoded credentials. Rotate before deleting.

## Required for Production (not yet all implemented)

- Helmet security headers
- express-rate-limit on auth routes
- express-mongo-sanitize
- CSRF tokens on forms
- SESSION_SECRET required in all non-test environments

Reference: `docs/security/SECURITY_AUDIT.md`
